frame0.consensus_text: Kensington house is Hanging with mourning - the P. of Denmarke comes dayly to Court and
on tuesday seuerall [several] of the Nobillity [Nobility] paid the Princess <sw-del>& Capta ley who was Lately</sw-del>
visset [visit?] at Bartlet House <brev-y>th</brev-y><sl>e</sl> same day Capt Birch dyed [died] suddenly of an apoplexy & Capt<sw-ex>ain</sw-ex> Hussey

who was Lately wounded by Mr Hall is at the Point of Death <brev-y>th</brev-y><sl>e</sl> D<sw-ex>uke</sw-ex> of Srewsbury [Shrewsbury] is gone to

an account that the Queene Dowager of
England is alsoe Dead - the Dauphine has
now sent a present to the Electoress of Ba=
varia consisting of the Portraiture of the
3 Dukes his sons a Tea table with Dishes

Rare things to the value of 500000 Livers
wee are fortifieing [fortifying] all our sea ports in
Province to prevent there [their?] being bombarded
by the English
Middleburgh ditto one of our Privateres
hath brough in here 7 ffrench prisses some
of which are laden with Naval Stores
Hague 20<sw-sup>th</sw-sup> wee have advice that the
venetians have sent 6 friggots to reinforce
